      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The weight you're carrying is real, but it's not proof that you can't be a person; it's proof you've been through so much that the old definition of \"worth\" has shattered.\nYou don't need to have anything left to give to the world to still exist as a human being, even if that existence currently feels hollow and heavy.\nSometimes the only way to stop dragging this empty thing is to let someone else hold it for you, so you can finally rest.",
